## Security Rules (hard blocks)

- No credentials, tokens, or secrets committed in any file (including test fixtures and `.tfvars`)
- `process.env` must not be accessed outside the config service
- All controller endpoints require an auth guard, except explicitly public routes (e.g. health check, API docs)
- No SQL built via string interpolation — use parameterised queries or ORM query builders
- No hardcoded external service URLs or resource IDs in source code
- No IAM policy with `*` action and `*` resource
- No public network exposure (`0.0.0.0/0` ingress, public bucket, public DB) without a documented justification in a proposal
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` or equivalent for user-supplied content
- Lockfile changes must correspond to an intentional dependency change

---

## Testing Requirements

### Backend
- Unit tests for all service methods — mock external clients and ORM repositories
- Do not test controllers directly — test services
- Integration tests for critical API endpoints using a mock or test database
- Tests describe behaviour, not implementation, in their names
- No shared mutable state between tests

### Frontend
- Unit tests for all significant components
- Unit tests for state stores in isolation
- No logic under test should hit a real network

### Infrastructure
- Non-trivial IaC modules have tests (Terratest / `terraform test` / Pulumi unit tests)
- Every PR touching infra includes the `terraform plan` (or equivalent) summary in the PR description

